rComments: Took as elective towards my engineering degree. No complaints. Stress free course. Just do the readings and show up and you'll be fine.

Professor Russell is a caring professor and he makes himself readily available for students. his class was extremely LECTURE heavy so take great notes and listen to his insights. he's also very knowledgeable, and provides several small and low-stakes extra credit assignments. I take the exam in 1 hour, after which point I may like him a little less
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Graded by few things', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Attendance seems to be very important to him, which is pure torture, but even if you do attend and write exactly what he said, he still might fail you. However, I did good on all papers and still received the lowest final grade possible. It's a true mystery. I dropped second course with him because he retroactively changed my grade for 1st paper.

rComments: Pretty light general course work, lectures could get boring but covered some interesting topics. Nice guy, a bit tough on paper grading though.

PHI107 was an immensely fascinating class, and Prof. really did a great job teaching it! The textbook is extremely cheap ($30), and the readings are gone over thoroughly in class the following week. I appreciate this professor's ability to review difficult concepts and answer questions directly and with clear reasoning.
I really like this course, clear and concise, prof Russell is very nice and wants students to succeed

Really boring, really easy. Go to the lectures and understand the concepts, boring and simple as they may be, and you're basically handed a 4.0.
Amazing prof! Cares a lot about students and is very approachable. Very clear in explaining concepts.

Prof wasn't the most experienced but still seemed to care, overall content/assigned readings were interesting/thought-provoking. You're prone to falling asleep in lectures because simple stuff is retold a hundred times, would prefer a faster pace.
